public class SBMLsqueezer<T>
extends de.zbit.Launcher

The main program of SBMLsqueezer. This class initializes all required objects, starts the GUI if desired and loads all settings from the user.

squeeze

public void squeeze(Object sbmlSource,
                    String outfile,
                    boolean searchSABIO)
             throws Throwable
Reads in the given SBML file, squeezes kinetic equations in and writes the result back to the given SBML file. This method only works if SBMLsqueezer is used as a stand-alone program.

Parameters:
sbmlSource - the path to a file that contains SBML code or another object that can be read by the current reader used by SBMLsqueezer.
outfile - The absolute path to a file where the result should be stored. This must be a file that ends with .xml or .sbml (case insensitive).
searchSABIO - Also search for kinetics in SABIO-RK and add them if possible
Throws:
Throwable
